The paper deals with crowd counting using convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves incorporating 3D convolution kernels and global contextual information, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on benchmark datasets and a vehicle dataset, which suggests that it may fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) categories as well.
